Depends: libfontconfig1, libssl3, libicu72 | libicu76 | libicu74, indi-bin, python3-venv, python3-pip, adduser, systemd
Recommends: indi-full, astap, phd2, siril, xpra, xserver-xorg-video-dummy, dphys-swapfile, lsof
Suggests: graxpert
Description: N.I.N.A. Polaris astrophotography server
 Browser-controlled astrophotography controller for Raspberry Pi,
 mini-PCs, and other small Linux hosts. Provides full equipment +
 capture + processing workflow without a desktop, accessible from
 any device with a web browser on the LAN.
 .
 Includes embedded INDI driver management (via indi-web), automatic
 plate-solving (ASTAP), PHD2 guider integration, live stacking, batch
 calibration, color combine, and a Lightroom-style image editor. AI
 post-processing (GraXpert ONNX models) runs in the client browser
 via WebGPU, taking compute load off the Pi.
 .
 Bundles a self-contained .NET 10 runtime so no separate dotnet
 install is required. Runs as a system user 'polaris' with captures
 written to /home/polaris/files by default.
